pokemon.name: victini
pokemon.text_entry: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

pokemon.name: snivy
pokemon.text_entry: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

pokemon.name: servine
pokemon.text_entry: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

pokemon.name: serperior
pokemon.text_entry: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

pokemon.name: tepig
pokemon.text_entry: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

pokemon.name: pignite
pokemon.text_entry: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

pokemon.name: emboar
pokemon.text_entry: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

pokemon.name: oshawott
pokemon.text_entry: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

pokemon.name: dewott
pokemon.text_entry: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

pokemon.name: samurott
pokemon.text_entry: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

pokemon.name: patrat
pokemon.text_entry: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.

pokemon.name: watchog
pokemon.text_entry: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

pokemon.name: lillipup
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

pokemon.name: herdier
pokemon.text_entry: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

pokemon.name: stoutland
pokemon.text_entry: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

pokemon.name: purrloin
pokemon.text_entry: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

pokemon.name: liepard
pokemon.text_entry: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

pokemon.name: pansage
pokemon.text_entry: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.

pokemon.name: simisage
pokemon.text_entry: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

pokemon.name: pansear
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: simisear
pokemon.text_entry: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

pokemon.name: panpour
pokemon.text_entry: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

pokemon.name: simipour
pokemon.text_entry: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

pokemon.name: munna
pokemon.text_entry: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.

pokemon.name: musharna
pokemon.text_entry: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.

pokemon.name: pidove
pokemon.text_entry: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.

pokemon.name: tranquill
pokemon.text_entry: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.

pokemon.name: unfezant
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is intelligent and intensely proud. People will sit up and take notice if you become the Trainer of one.

pokemon.name: blitzle
pokemon.text_entry: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

pokemon.name: zebstrika
pokemon.text_entry: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

pokemon.name: roggenrola
pokemon.text_entry: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

pokemon.name: boldore
pokemon.text_entry: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.

pokemon.name: gigalith
pokemon.text_entry: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.

pokemon.name: woobat
pokemon.text_entry: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.

pokemon.name: swoobat
pokemon.text_entry: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

pokemon.name: drilbur
pokemon.text_entry: It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.

pokemon.name: excadrill
pokemon.text_entry: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.

pokemon.name: audino
pokemon.text_entry: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

pokemon.name: timburr
pokemon.text_entry: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.

pokemon.name: gurdurr
pokemon.text_entry: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

pokemon.name: conkeldurr
pokemon.text_entry: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.

pokemon.name: tympole
pokemon.text_entry: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.

pokemon.name: palpitoad
pokemon.text_entry: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

pokemon.name: seismitoad
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.

pokemon.name: throh
pokemon.text_entry: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.

pokemon.name: sawk
pokemon.text_entry: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.

pokemon.name: sewaddle
pokemon.text_entry: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

pokemon.name: swadloon
pokemon.text_entry: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

pokemon.name: leavanny
pokemon.text_entry: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

pokemon.name: venipede
pokemon.text_entry: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.

pokemon.name: whirlipede
pokemon.text_entry: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.

pokemon.name: scolipede
pokemon.text_entry: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.

pokemon.name: cottonee
pokemon.text_entry: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.

pokemon.name: whimsicott
pokemon.text_entry: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.

pokemon.name: petilil
pokemon.text_entry: The deeper the color of a Petilil’s leaves, the healthier the Pokémon is. Petilil sometimes makes its home in a well-tended field or flowerbed.

pokemon.name: lilligant
pokemon.text_entry: Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they’re also staggeringly expensive.

pokemon.name: basculin-red-striped
pokemon.text_entry: Known for their violence, these Pokémon have the most fights with schools of red- striped Basculin.

pokemon.name: sandile
pokemon.text_entry: Sandile is small, but its legs and lower body are powerful. Pushing sand aside as it goes, Sandile moves through the desert as if it’s swimming.

pokemon.name: krokorok
pokemon.text_entry: Although this Pokémon has specialized eyes that allow it to see in the dark, Krokorok won’t move much at night—the desert gets cold after sunset.

pokemon.name: krookodile
pokemon.text_entry: While terribly aggressive, Krookodile also has the patience to stay hidden under sand for days, lying in wait for prey.

pokemon.name: darumaka
pokemon.text_entry: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.

pokemon.name: darmanitan-standard
pokemon.text_entry: When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.

pokemon.name: maractus
pokemon.text_entry: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

pokemon.name: dwebble
pokemon.text_entry: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

pokemon.name: crustle
pokemon.text_entry: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.

pokemon.name: scraggy
pokemon.text_entry: It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.

pokemon.name: scrafty
pokemon.text_entry: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.

pokemon.name: sigilyph
pokemon.text_entry: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

pokemon.name: yamask
pokemon.text_entry: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

pokemon.name: cofagrigus
pokemon.text_entry: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.

pokemon.name: tirtouga
pokemon.text_entry: Its hunting grounds encompassed a broad area, from the land to more than half a mile deep in the ocean.

pokemon.name: carracosta
pokemon.text_entry: Carracosta eats every last bit of the prey it catches, even the shells and bones, to further strengthen its sturdy shell.

pokemon.name: archen
pokemon.text_entry: Restored from a fossil, this ancient bird Pokémon has wings but can’t yet fly.

pokemon.name: archeops
pokemon.text_entry: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, the muscles it uses to flap its wings are still weak, so it needs a long runway in order to take off.

pokemon.name: trubbish
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.

pokemon.name: garbodor
pokemon.text_entry: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.

pokemon.name: zorua
pokemon.text_entry: Zorua sometimes transforms into a person and goes into cities to search for food. When Zorua does this, it usually takes on the form of a child.

pokemon.name: zoroark
pokemon.text_entry: Seeking to ease the burden of their solitude, lonely Trainers tell Zoroark to show illusions to them.

pokemon.name: minccino
pokemon.text_entry: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.

pokemon.name: cinccino
pokemon.text_entry: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.

pokemon.name: gothita
pokemon.text_entry: Even when nobody seems to be around, Gothita can still be heard making a muted cry. Many believe it’s speaking to something only it can see.

pokemon.name: gothorita
pokemon.text_entry: On nights when the stars shine, this Pokémon’s psychic power is at its strongest. It’s unknown just what link Gothorita has to the greater universe.

pokemon.name: gothitelle
pokemon.text_entry: A criminal who was shown his fate by a Gothitelle went missing that same day and was never seen again.

pokemon.name: solosis
pokemon.text_entry: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokémon’s body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.

pokemon.name: duosion
pokemon.text_entry: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.

pokemon.name: reuniclus
pokemon.text_entry: It’s said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.

pokemon.name: ducklett
pokemon.text_entry: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

pokemon.name: swanna
pokemon.text_entry: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

pokemon.name: vanillite
pokemon.text_entry: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

pokemon.name: vanillish
pokemon.text_entry: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.

pokemon.name: vanilluxe
pokemon.text_entry: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: deerling
pokemon.text_entry: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

pokemon.name: sawsbuck
pokemon.text_entry: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

pokemon.name: emolga
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.

pokemon.name: karrablast
pokemon.text_entry: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.

pokemon.name: escavalier
pokemon.text_entry: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.

pokemon.name: foongus
pokemon.text_entry: The spores released from this Pokémon’s hands are highly poisonous, but when thoroughly dried, the spores can be used as stomach medicine.

pokemon.name: amoonguss
pokemon.text_entry: Amoonguss generally doesn’t move much. It tends to stand still near Poké Balls that have been dropped on the ground.

pokemon.name: frillish
pokemon.text_entry: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

pokemon.name: jellicent
pokemon.text_entry: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

pokemon.name: alomomola
pokemon.text_entry: The reason it helps Pokémon in a weakened condition is that any Pokémon coming after them may also attack Alomomola.

pokemon.name: joltik
pokemon.text_entry: Joltik latch on to other Pokémon and suck out static electricity. They’re often found sticking to Yamper’s hindquarters.

pokemon.name: galvantula
pokemon.text_entry: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokémon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.

pokemon.name: ferroseed
pokemon.text_entry: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.

pokemon.name: ferrothorn
pokemon.text_entry: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.

pokemon.name: klink
pokemon.text_entry: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.

pokemon.name: klang
pokemon.text_entry: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.

pokemon.name: klinklang
pokemon.text_entry: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.

pokemon.name: tynamo
pokemon.text_entry: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

pokemon.name: eelektrik
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

pokemon.name: eelektross
pokemon.text_entry: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

pokemon.name: elgyem
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.

pokemon.name: beheeyem
pokemon.text_entry: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

pokemon.name: litwick
pokemon.text_entry: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.

pokemon.name: lampent
pokemon.text_entry: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.

pokemon.name: chandelure
pokemon.text_entry: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.

pokemon.name: axew
pokemon.text_entry: They play with each other by knocking their large tusks together. Their tusks break sometimes, but they grow back so quickly that it isn’t a concern.

pokemon.name: fraxure
pokemon.text_entry: Its skin is as hard as a suit of armor. Fraxure’s favorite strategy is to tackle its opponents, stabbing them with its tusks at the same time.

pokemon.name: haxorus
pokemon.text_entry: While usually kindhearted, it can be terrifying if angered. Tusks that can slice through steel beams are how Haxorus deals with its adversaries.

pokemon.name: cubchoo
pokemon.text_entry: It sniffles before performing a move, using its frosty snot to provide an icy element to any move that needs it.

pokemon.name: beartic
pokemon.text_entry: It swims energetically through frigid seas. When it gets tired, it freezes the seawater with its breath so it can rest on the ice.

pokemon.name: cryogonal
pokemon.text_entry: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: shelmet
pokemon.text_entry: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.

pokemon.name: accelgor
pokemon.text_entry: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.

pokemon.name: stunfisk
pokemon.text_entry: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

pokemon.name: mienfoo
pokemon.text_entry: Though small, Mienfoo’s temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.

pokemon.name: mienshao
pokemon.text_entry: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokémon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.

pokemon.name: druddigon
pokemon.text_entry: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

pokemon.name: golett
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.

pokemon.name: golurk
pokemon.text_entry: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.

pokemon.name: pawniard
pokemon.text_entry: A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

pokemon.name: bisharp
pokemon.text_entry: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.

pokemon.name: bouffalant
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

pokemon.name: rufflet
pokemon.text_entry: A combative Pokémon, it’s ready to pick a fight with anyone. It has talons that can crush hard berries.

pokemon.name: braviary
pokemon.text_entry: Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent, it’s Corviknight that’s taken the role of transportation in Galar.

pokemon.name: vullaby
pokemon.text_entry: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.

pokemon.name: mandibuzz
pokemon.text_entry: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.

pokemon.name: heatmor
pokemon.text_entry: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

pokemon.name: durant
pokemon.text_entry: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

pokemon.name: deino
pokemon.text_entry: Because it can’t see, this Pokémon is constantly biting at everything it touches, trying to keep track of its surroundings.

pokemon.name: zweilous
pokemon.text_entry: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

pokemon.name: hydreigon
pokemon.text_entry: The three heads take turns sinking their teeth into the opponent. Their attacks won’t slow until their target goes down.

pokemon.name: larvesta
pokemon.text_entry: Larvesta’s body is warm all over. It spouts fire from the tips of its horns to intimidate predators and scare prey.

pokemon.name: volcarona
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon emerges from a cocoon formed of raging flames. Ancient murals depict Volcarona as a deity of fire.

pokemon.name: cobalion
pokemon.text_entry: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

pokemon.name: terrakion
pokemon.text_entry: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

pokemon.name: virizion
pokemon.text_entry: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

pokemon.name: tornadus-incarnate
pokemon.text_entry: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

pokemon.name: thundurus-incarnate
pokemon.text_entry: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

pokemon.name: reshiram
pokemon.text_entry: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

pokemon.name: zekrom
pokemon.text_entry: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom’s lightning.

pokemon.name: landorus-incarnate
pokemon.text_entry: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

pokemon.name: kyurem
pokemon.text_entry: The sameness of Zekrom’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.

pokemon.name: keldeo-ordinary
pokemon.text_entry: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

pokemon.name: meloetta-aria
pokemon.text_entry: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

pokemon.name: genesect
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
